resolution: "Converted publishing to idempotent tag-driven npm provenance publication and added exact-version registry, npx, Bun install, and bunx verification before GitHub release creation."
expected_result: One tagged artifact is correctly available to npm and Bun consumers.
actual_result: Packed artifact proof passed through npx and bunx; workflow publishes once to the npm registry and verifies the exact published version separately with npm and Bun.
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T17:38:16.562Z",codex-root,"bun run release:dry-run passed installation and launcher checks from the packed tarball through both npx and bunx."
  "2026-07-21T17:51:49.817Z",codex-root,"PR review hardening: registry polling now tolerates invalid or empty JSON and uses Node Atomics.wait instead of a bash sleep subprocess."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T17:32:47.206Z",codex-root,Bun uses the npm registry for this package; one provenance-backed npm publish plus exact-version Bun installation is the correct dual-ecosystem delivery model.
